sec.p:
The normalized difference vegetation index (NDVI) has been used to indicate the greenness of vegetation in numerous vegetation studies (e.g.,  DeFries et al., 2000; Loveland et al., 2000; Breshears et al., 2005; Tucker et al., 2005; Zhou et al., 2014). As a coarse measure, the differences in NDVI may mask changes to vegetation species composition; however, it has limited influences on identifying vegetation types. It is defined as \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
